1
00:00:07,260 --> 00:00:10,700
Have you ever heard about that

2
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:13,580
the cliff of a snow mountain

3
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:19,220
once fascinated numerous people?

4
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:24,140
Legend has it that,

5
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:26,940
there were treasures at the peak

6
00:00:27,780 --> 00:00:32,860
but also there was a bottomless chasm hidden over there.

7
00:00:34,460 --> 00:00:37,900
The smart, the fool

8
00:00:37,940 --> 00:00:40,740
and the kind people,

9
00:00:41,380 --> 00:00:47,220
all are familiar to you.

10
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:51,660
On the mountainside, on the cliff,

11
00:00:51,980 --> 00:00:54,580
on the cloud,

12
00:00:54,980 --> 00:01:00,100
and in the human world,

13
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:19,220
snowflakes are drifting profusely and disorderly.

14
00:01:30,980 --> 00:01:34,980
Joy of Life Season 1

15
00:01:34,980 --> 00:01:37,900
Episode 26

16
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,510
Dad, you want to see me.

17
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:46,080
You're back.

18
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,270
Come and take a seat.

19
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:52,720
The negotiation

20
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,830
in Court of State Ceremonials is over.

21
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:56,550
Be cautious at the Hall tomorrow.

22
00:01:57,510 --> 00:01:58,310
You mean

23
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:00,230
the banquet tomorrow night?

24
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,230
What's wrong?

25
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:07,310
It's known to the world that

26
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,630
literary giants are all in Beiqi.

27
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,830
In earlier years,

28
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:14,320
scholars actually found it an honor

29
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:17,110
to pass the imperial examinations in Beiqi.

30
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,190
Though things are better these years,

31
00:02:19,390 --> 00:02:20,880
when it comes to scholars,

32
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:24,240
Nanqing is no match to Beiqi.

33
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:28,110
Now the Nanqing literary circles

34
00:02:28,270 --> 00:02:29,800
have anchored their hopes on you.

35
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:33,440
Me?

36
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:35,600
The literary circles?

37
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:38,030
That poem with the line

38
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,240
“A thousand miles from home, I'm grieved at
autumn's plight” which you wrote a few days ago

39
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:41,630
is rated as the No.1 Current Seven-character Poem

40
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:44,080
by scholars of Nanqing.

41
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:48,110
Many say in private that

42
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,880
accomplished at such a young age,

43
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:54,190
you can be better than Zhuang Mohan in future.

44
00:02:54,190 --> 00:02:55,750
I just wrote one poem.

45
00:02:55,830 --> 00:02:56,830
They are too hasty in drawing the conclusion.

46
00:02:57,270 --> 00:02:59,030
One poem is not much,

47
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,720
but we've longed for a talented scholar

48
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,520
for so long.

49
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:06,390
We may even fight a losing battle.

50
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:07,880
Who will lose?

51
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,800
You, of course.

52
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,960
So tomorrow night,

53
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,830
everyone will watch me

54
00:03:15,110 --> 00:03:18,030
meeting the literary giant

55
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,320
Zhuang Mohan.

56
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:22,800
You don't need to be amazing.

57
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:25,670
Just play it safe.

58
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,800
That's enough.

59
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:31,670
Will you go tomorrow night?

60
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:33,960
The banquet tomorrow

61
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,160
is especially set for Court of State Ceremonials

62
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,520
and Board of Rites.

63
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:40,270
I'm the Assistant Minister of Ministry of Revenue.

64
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,550
Why would I go?

65
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:44,440
Don't worry.

66
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:46,960
Just a little advice.

67
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:49,830
Respected as Zhuang Mohan is,

68
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,630
why would he actually make things difficult

69
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:53,440
for a young man like you?

70
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,880
Fan Xian will also attend the banquet tomorrow night.

71
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:39,550
Master Zhuang, please ruin his name.

72
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:00,830
You've hung up a red lantern.

73
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:03,920
Uncle, for all these years,

74
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:05,600
I've been wondering

75
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:07,480
whether you can see or not.

76
00:05:07,670 --> 00:05:08,720
How come you know

77
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,350
I hang up a lantern?

78
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:10,440
And you even know the color.

79
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,640
It's hard for me to explain.

80
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:15,790
I can know everything.

81
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,720
But I don't see with eyes.

82
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,440
You see with your heart.

83
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,270
I don't know how to put it.

84
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,790
Uncle.

85
00:05:27,110 --> 00:05:28,720
I find you mysterious all the time.

86
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,950
If anyone dares to piss you off,

87
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:31,830
he's definitely dice with death.

88
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:37,790
Take a seat. Take a seat. Take a seat.

89
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:43,720
Let's get down to business.

90
00:05:45,110 --> 00:05:46,110
Tomorrow night,

91
00:05:46,110 --> 00:05:47,950
the imperial family will hold a banquet at
the Hall of Prayer for Good Harvest.

92
00:05:48,070 --> 00:05:49,040
The Hall of Prayer for Good Harvest?

93
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:51,200
How is Wang Qinian involved?
(Qinian sounds like Prayer for Good Harvest in Chinese)

94
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,200
Who?

95
00:05:52,390 --> 00:05:53,270
Wang Qinian.

96
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:55,880
Uncle,

97
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:58,480
besides being mysterious,

98
00:05:58,640 --> 00:05:59,550
how come your thoughts

99
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:00,390
are so hard to follow recently?

100
00:06:01,390 --> 00:06:02,110
Thoughts?

101
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:08,920
I don't think the Hall of Prayer for Good Harvest

102
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,040
has anything to do with Wang Qinian.

103
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,830
Fine.

104
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,070
Let's get down to business.

105
00:06:14,350 --> 00:06:16,000
The banquet tomorrow is mainly for

106
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,600
the celebration of finishing the war against Beiqi.

107
00:06:19,230 --> 00:06:20,350
It's kind of a big event.

108
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:22,640
Aren't you going to ask me

109
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,000
why I ask you over?

110
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,670
Aren't you going to tell me if I don't ask?

111
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,000
You've made a point.

112
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:33,270
Fine.

113
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:35,640
After the banquet tomorrow night,

114
00:06:35,790 --> 00:06:37,000
we'll break into the imperial harem.

115
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:37,880
Are you sure?

116
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,600
Everyone will relax

117
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,600
after a great event.

118
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:43,830
OK, the plan remains unchanged.

119
00:06:44,110 --> 00:06:45,440
I will lure away Hong Sixiang,

120
00:06:45,670 --> 00:06:47,000
and you should sneak into the Empress Dowager's palace

121
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:47,760
to find the key.

122
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,160
There's one last problem.

123
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:50,230
I don't know

124
00:06:50,230 --> 00:06:51,510
where the Empress Dowager keeps the key.

125
00:06:51,790 --> 00:06:53,920
It might take time to find it.

126
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,830
There's a secret compartment

127
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:57,110
on the bed board under her pillow.

128
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,720
All her important things are kept there.

129
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,230
How do you know that?

130
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,440
Your mom searched it before.

131
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:05,760
Why did my mom

132
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:06,720
search her secret compartment?

133
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:11,720
The old lady has lived in widowhood for so many years.

134
00:07:12,110 --> 00:07:13,440
Though she looks serious,

135
00:07:13,790 --> 00:07:14,880
I wonder whether she keeps

136
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,640
love letters in private or not.

137
00:07:19,790 --> 00:07:21,880
Those are the words said by your mom back then.

138
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,880
So she searched the Empress Dowager's

139
00:07:25,270 --> 00:07:27,230
secret compartment only for gossiping!

140
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,880
I've no idea

141
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:29,950
what gossiping implies,

142
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,160
but yes, you're right.

143
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,320
Didn't she get caught?

144
00:07:33,550 --> 00:07:34,830
I kept watch for her.

145
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:41,110
Why are you laughing?

146
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,350
Words can't express

147
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:44,880
my feelings right now.

148
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,440
What feelings?

149
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,390
Just forget it.

150
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:49,950
Anyway, back then,

151
00:07:50,110 --> 00:07:50,720
my mom had solved

152
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,640
the biggest problem for me.

153
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:52,640
Now,

154
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,920
as long as I know where the key is,

155
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,550
I feel quite sure of getting it out.

156
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:58,480
If we take the key,

157
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,270
the old lady might notice.

158
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:01,670
We'd better put in a fake one.

159
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:03,390
Without seeing the real key,

160
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:05,070
how could you make a fake one in advance?

161
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,440
I've got an idea.

162
00:08:06,670 --> 00:08:07,320
Good.

163
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,670
Wait for me here tomorrow night.

164
00:08:12,110 --> 00:08:13,200
Someone's here.

165
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:15,670
I asked him over.

166
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:17,510
Seriously?

167
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:22,510
Your Excellency.

168
00:08:22,510 --> 00:08:23,200
Come in.

169
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:25,270
It's quite late now.

170
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,510
Do you have anything for me?

171
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:27,950
I have a question for you.

172
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:29,790
Please go ahead.

173
00:08:31,230 --> 00:08:33,960
Do you have anything to do with the
Hall of Prayer for Good Harvest?

174
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,440
I suppose not.

175
00:08:37,910 --> 00:08:38,790
I think so.

176
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:41,280
What's wrong?

177
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:42,230
Nothing.

178
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:44,790
Take a seat.

179
00:08:45,470 --> 00:08:46,320
Your Excellency, thank you.

180
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:47,520
I might as well stand.

181
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,470
Your Excellency,

182
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:56,200
I heard that by deterring the Beiqi mission

183
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,760
in the Court of State Ceremonials,

184
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,200
you've made great contributions to Nanqing.

185
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:01,550
=Ten taels of silver=

186
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,550
I will attend the banquet tomorrow night.

187
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:04,760
Your Excellency, charismatic and vigorous as you are,

188
00:09:04,910 --> 00:09:06,640
you'll definitely be promoted in the near future.

189
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:07,710
Is this for me?

190
00:09:07,710 --> 00:09:08,400
Yes.

191
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,230
Thank you, Your Excellency.

192
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:15,440
Your Excellency,

193
00:09:15,760 --> 00:09:17,110
next time you grant me a reward,

194
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,590
please grant me bank notes instead.

195
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,080
They are easier to hide.

196
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,110
I want to break into the imperial harem at night.

197
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:22,710
Your Excellency,

198
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:24,790
pardon, please?

199
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,960
I said I want to break into the imperial harem at night

200
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:29,320
and sneak into the Empress Dowager's palace

201
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,710
to steal a key.

202
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:32,000
Of course,

203
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,400
for fear the old lady might notice,

204
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:35,200
I have to make a fake key overnight

205
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:35,840
to replace the real one.

206
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,030
That's my plan.

207
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,590
Are you kidding me?

208
00:09:40,670 --> 00:09:41,350
Not really.

209
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,470
Are you serious?

210
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,470
Yes.

211
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,670
It's a deadly sin which could implicate your family.

212
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,670
I suppose it is.

213
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:54,110
Then why do you

214
00:09:54,110 --> 00:09:55,520
tell me about it?

215
00:09:55,710 --> 00:09:56,790
I just told you

216
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,400
I have to make a fake key

217
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,280
overnight.

218
00:09:59,350 --> 00:10:00,760
I have to find the best locksmith in the capital city.

219
00:10:01,230 --> 00:10:02,350
Since I'm not familiar with the capital city,

220
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:03,640
I need someone with connections.

221
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:04,840
That's you.

222
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,030
If I'm involved,

223
00:10:11,030 --> 00:10:12,320
I will also commit a deadly sin.

224
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:14,710
You just find me a locksmith

225
00:10:14,710 --> 00:10:15,640
to make a key.

226
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:16,790
You know nothing else.

227
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:17,880
Right!

228
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,350
Then you should only ask me

229
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:20,110
to find a locksmith.

230
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:21,590
Right? Why tell me

231
00:10:21,590 --> 00:10:22,350
the whole plan?

232
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:23,790
I also want to tell you less,

233
00:10:24,350 --> 00:10:25,350
but I can't.

234
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,840
You have to wait for me

235
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,110
outside the imperial palace tomorrow.

236
00:10:30,150 --> 00:10:31,030
Your Excellency!

237
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:37,470
Aren't you afraid that I might tell on you?

238
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,840
Do you really want to

239
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,200
trust me

240
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,230
with your life?

241
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:42,640
Of course I do.

242
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:44,440
You're a wise man.

243
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,110
You should know that

244
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,440
you only need to take a little risk by helping me,

245
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:53,030
but you'll get yourself killed if you dare betray me.

246
00:10:54,470 --> 00:10:55,440
What do you mean?

247
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,150
You know how Chen Pingping

248
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:58,000
treats me.

249
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,320
The Head treats you like his son.

250
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,520
So this is the case.

251
00:11:07,470 --> 00:11:08,670
If I tell on you

252
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:09,760
and get you killed,

253
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:11,840
the Head will definitely

254
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,590
cut me into pieces.

255
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,150
You're really wise.

256
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,400
Then why don't you ask the Head

257
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,400
to do you the favor.

258
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:21,150
It's inconvenient for big potatoes

259
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:22,230
to do such things.

260
00:11:27,230 --> 00:11:28,230
What can I say?

261
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,030
The choice is yours.

262
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,550
I know a good locksmith.

263
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:33,080
Good. Ask him to wait for me tomorrow night.

264
00:11:33,590 --> 00:11:34,280
OK.

265
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,670
From tonight on,

266
00:11:36,670 --> 00:11:38,400
I'll raise your salary by another ten taels of silver.

267
00:11:40,030 --> 00:11:41,840
This is something that might get my entire family killed.

268
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:42,840
You only add ten taels of silver?!

269
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,000
Don't you think it's too little?

270
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:44,590
So you don't want it?

271
00:11:44,590 --> 00:11:45,590
I want it.

272
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:48,590
Give me bank notes instead next time.

273
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,230
What time is it now?

274
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,280
It's about 1:00 p.m.

275
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:08,960
Is the Hall of Prayer for Good Harvest ready?

276
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:11,280
Yes, they started decorating

277
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,320
early this morning.

278
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:17,030
Find me a place for the night banquet.

279
00:12:18,710 --> 00:12:19,790
It's only held for Court of State Ceremonials

280
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:20,880
and Board of Rites.

281
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,320
It's no big deal.

282
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:23,670
Just do it.

283
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:25,470
Yes.

284
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,200
I can't wait.

285
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,590
I've asked.

286
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:39,840
